oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Waylon Jennings Press Release: Version 1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Jennings, Waylon; Moeller Talent, Inc.; Offset printing;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: One color offset printing plate (black on silver) advertising Waylon Jennings and containing a biography of his life and accomplishments. The press release describes his entry into the entertainment world at age 12, playing with Buddy Holly, return to Lubbock as a deejay, move to Phoenix, playing with The Waylors, signing with RCA Victor, songs recorded, and move to Nashville. The press release also contains a photograph of Waylon Jennings.
